  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "jshell-401-intro",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "# JShell 401 — Modern Java Features\n\n> **Requires Java 17+.** Venus Notebooks uses Java 21, so all features in this notebook are fully supported and stable.\n\nJava has accelerated its release cadence since Java 9 (one release every 6 months). Each LTS version brings major language improvements. This notebook covers the most impactful features from Java 14–21.\n\n| Feature | Since (stable) | Why it matters |\n|---|---|---|\n| `record` | Java 16 | Immutable data classes in one line |\n| Text blocks | Java 15 | Multi-line strings without `\\n` escapes |\n| `switch` expressions | Java 14 | Switch that returns a value, no fall-through |\n| Pattern matching `instanceof` | Java 16 | Eliminates redundant cast after instanceof |\n| Sealed classes | Java 17 | Restrict which classes can extend yours |\n| `var` in lambdas | Java 11 | Annotations on lambda parameters |\n| Record patterns | Java 21 | Destructure records in patterns |",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
